cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with face clustering, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a clustering algorithm that uses a Conditional Random Field (CRF) model, which is a machine learning technique, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a representation based on ResNet, which is a deep learning architecture, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its algorithm on two benchmark face datasets, indicating that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a k-NN variant of its algorithm, which has a linear time complexity, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
